 "verdict": "REDUCED_SEED_RECOVERS_CV",
 "headline": "On opaque Linear B, semi-supervised label spreading with as few as 3 CORRECT vowel seed(s) (+3 consonant anchors) recovers held-out C/V at AUC>=0.75 (vs the fully-unsupervised NULL ARI~0.005 / AUC~0.57 and the supervised ceiling 0.835). The purely typological FREQUENCY-prior seeding does NOT reach the bar (min k=None) because the literal most-frequent signs are noisy vowel proxies (precision-at-top low). => the LA C/V partition needs a SMALL number of CORRECT external anchors, which frequency alone cannot reliably supply."
